As I&#39;ve mentioned in the comments, position of a component in a GridLayout defined by a `top` value in `css`. So you would need to change it if you want to re-position(remove space, in this case) an element. The problem here is that 

- GridLayout not necessary starts from top, so you would need to figure out a correct value for a top,
- and then you would need to differentiate a correct component(label in this case) using `:n-th` child, since a class name applied to a component, is not propagated to  a parent&#39;s `v-gridlayout-slot`.

