You can comment it in the same way as you do in a functions file or in a class file.

Below you can find different approaches:

First Method

    &lt;?php /* Put a comment here */ &gt;
    &lt;?php   if($can_follow_company): ?&gt; 

        Code

    &lt;?php endif; ?&gt;
    
Second Method (A more beautiful comment with annonations):

    &lt;?php
     /**
      * @todo lorem ipsum
      * @Author 
      */
    &gt;
    &lt;?php   if($can_follow_company): ?&gt; 

        Code

    &lt;?php endif; ?&gt;


You can also put the comment just before the if statement, but for second option is what is defined as the best way to comment and document `PHP` code as in this way you can use your IDE or tools to generate documentation [https://www.phpdoc.org/][1].


**UPDATE FROM COMMENTS**

If you need to just not execute the **Code** part you just need to add a false to if statement. Your code would be like this;

    &lt;?php   if($can_follow_company &amp;&amp; false): ?&gt; 

        Code

    &lt;?php endif; ?&gt;


  [1]: https://www.phpdoc.org/

